question: Will Tesla deliver a Cybertruck in Q3?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if Tesla, Inc. or a high-ranking Tesla executive (CEO, CFO, COO, or a Vice President) officially confirms that there was a delivery of a Cybertruck between July 1, 2023, and September 30, 2023. Confirmation must come in the form of an official statement, press release, or a public announcement by the aforementioned officials. Verified news reports citing these specific sources will also be considered. Such a confirmation, report, or announcement must be released prior to October 19, 2023, 12:00 PM ET.

Delivery refers to the Cybertruck being handed over to a customer, whether it is an individual or a business. This market is based solely on confirmed deliveries, and not on orders or production numbers.

If Tesla confirms a Cybertruck delivery before the end of Q3 2023, the market will resolve immediately to "Yes". If Tesla confirms that no Cybertruck will be delivered in Q3 2023 before the end of the quarter, the market will resolve immediately to "No". If no confirmation or denial is provided by Tesla as of the expiry date, the market will resolve to "No".

question: Will the Fed raise interest rates by 0 bps after its November meeting?
description:
The FED interest rates are defined in this market by the upper bound of the target federal funds range. The decisions on the target federal fund range are made by the Federal Open Market Committee (FOMC) meetings.

This market will resolve to “Yes” if following the Federal Reserve's November 2023 meeting the upper bound of the target federal funds rate is exactly the same as the level it was prior to the meeting (namely it increased 0 bps). Otherwise, it will resolve to “No.”

The resolution source for this market is the FOMC’s statement after its meeting scheduled for October 31 - November 1, 2023 according to the official calendar: https://www.federalreserve.gov/monetarypolicy/fomccalendars.htm.

The level and change of the target federal funds rate is also published at the official website of the Federal Reserve at https://www.federalreserve.gov/monetarypolicy/openmarket.htm.

This market may resolve as soon as the FOMC’s statement for their November meeting with relevant data is issued. If no statement is released by November 8, 2023, 11:59 PM ET, this market will resolve 50-50.

question: Will Puka Nacua be among the top 3 Wide Receivers in Week 3 Fantasy Football (PPR scoring)?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if Puka Nacua, the Los Angeles Rams Wide Receiver, achieves one of the top three highest fantasy points scores among all wide receivers during Week 3 of the current NFL season, following standard PPR scoring rules.

Standard PPR scoring rules consider not only points for each reception, but also for yards gained, touchdowns scored, and other performance factors. If Puka Nacua's total PPR score, as calculated under these rules, is among the top three highest among all wide receivers in Week 3, the market will resolve to "Yes". In the event of a tie for the third highest PPR score between Nacua and any other wide receiver, the market will resolve to "No".

The market will resolve immediately after the completion of the last NFL game of Week 3, regardless of any subsequent scoring revisions. If NFL Week 3 is not complete by October 4, 12:00 PM ET, this market will resolve to "No".

The resolution of this market will be based on the official statistics provided by Yahoo Fantasy Sports, accessible at their official website (https://sports.yahoo.com/fantasy/). In case of any discrepancies, the final resolution will be made based on the most reliable and widely accepted source, as decided by the Polymarket team.

question: Senate control after 2024 election?
description:
The 2024 United States Senate elections will be held on November 5, 2024, with 33 of the 100 seats in the Senate being contested.

This market will resolve to "Democrats" if following the 2024 U.S. Senate elections, Democrats have more than half of the voting Senate members, or half of the voting Senate members and a Democrat Vice President. It will resolve to "Republicans" under the same conditions for Republicans.

If the outcome of this election is ambiguous given the above rules, this market will remain open until the Majority Leader of the US Senate is selected following the 2024 US general election, at which point it will resolve to the party the majority leader is affiliated with at the time of their election to that position. If the elected majority leader does not caucus with either Democrats or Republicans, this market will resolve 50-50.

Determination of which party controls the Senate after the 2024 US Senate elections will be based on a consensus of credible reporting, or if there is ambiguity, final federal and/or state election authority certification or other final official determination of the 2024 election results.
